==Western Apache==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|[zàs]}}

===Etymology===

From Proto-Athabascan *''-wə̓t̕''. 

Cognates: Navajo ''-bid'', Plains Apache ''-bid''.

===Noun===
'''-bid'''

# [[belly]], [[stomach]], [[abdomen]]

The form '''-bid''' occurs in the San Carlos and Dilze’eh varieties; '''-big''' occurs in White Mountain.

